{"metadata": {"page_hash": "a0332f01431f9baa416acf18ca923c9b25469c9fa4834ab239479567da6ce66c", "original_filename": "1503.05621.pdf", "page_no": 27, "num_pages": 33, "original_width": 612, "original_height": 792, "coco_width": 1025, "coco_height": 1025, "collection": "arxiv_doublespaced", "doc_category": "scientific_articles"}, "form": [{"id_box": 27021, "box": [90.44117647058823, 74.62062121212136, 844.1179485294117, 75.62262342171698], "id_box_line": 0, "box_line": [90.44117647058823, 74.62062121212136, 844.1140629084966, 13.739490845959494], "text": "static algorithms, reinforcing our notion that overall MCMC efficiency is highly dependent upon", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/JJXYBJ+CMR12", "size": 11.9552001953125}}, {"id_box": 27021, "box": [90.44117647058823, 74.62062121212136, 844.1179485294117, 75.62262342171698], "id_box_line": 1, "box_line": [90.44117647058823, 105.56218750000005, 844.1179485294117, 13.739490845959608], "text": "hierarchical model structure, and attempting to infer what might be an efficient MCMC algorithm", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/JJXYBJ+CMR12", "size": 11.9552001953125}}, {"id_box": 27021, "box": [90.44117647058823, 74.62062121212136, 844.1179485294117, 75.62262342171698], "id_box_line": 2, "box_line": [90.44117647058823, 136.50375378787885, 404.74910253267973, 13.739490845959494], "text": "for a particular problem is, in general, difficult.", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/JJXYBJ+CMR12", "size": 11.9552001953125}}, {"id_box": 27022, "box": [90.44117647058823, 202.04086900252526, 196.59479901960788, 19.784687184343397], "id_box_line": 3, "box_line": [90.44117647058823, 202.04086900252526, 16.21855155228758, 19.784687184343397], "text": "5", "category": "Section-header", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/WOCEHX+CMBX12", "size": 17.21540069580078}}, {"id_box": 27022, "box": [90.44117647058823, 202.04086900252526, 196.59479901960788, 19.784687184343397], "id_box_line": 4, "box_line": [139.0968328022876, 202.04086900252526, 147.93914268790851, 19.784687184343397], "text": "Discussion", "category": "Section-header", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/WOCEHX+CMBX12", "size": 17.21540069580078}}, {"id_box": 27023, "box": [90.44117647058823, 253.02755271464662, 844.1259207516341, 261.2705198863635], "id_box_line": 5, "box_line": [90.44117647058823, 253.02755271464662, 844.1138619281046, 13.739490845959494], "text": "We have presented a general automated procedure for determining an \u201cefficient\u201d MCMC algorithm", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/JJXYBJ+CMR12", "size": 11.9552001953125}}, {"id_box": 27023, "box": [90.44117647058823, 253.02755271464662, 844.1259207516341, 261.2705198863635], "id_box_line": 6, "box_line": [90.44117647058823, 283.9691190025253, 844.1178480392157, 13.739490845959608], "text": "for hierarchical models. Our procedure is a greedy, iterative algorithm, which traverses a finite and", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/JJXYBJ+CMR12", "size": 11.9552001953125}}, {"id_box": 27023, "box": [90.44117647058823, 253.02755271464662, 844.1259207516341, 261.2705198863635], "id_box_line": 7, "box_line": [90.44117647058823, 314.910685290404, 844.1140629084966, 13.739490845959608], "text": "well-defined set of MCMC algorithms. This is the first such automated MCMC-generating proce-", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/JJXYBJ+CMR12", "size": 11.9552001953125}}, {"id_box": 27023, "box": [90.44117647058823, 253.02755271464662, 844.1259207516341, 261.2705198863635], "id_box_line": 8, "box_line": [90.44117647058823, 345.8522515782829, 844.1258202614379, 13.739490845959608], "text": "dure of its kind, so far as we are aware. Using a suite of example models, we have observed that our", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/JJXYBJ+CMR12", "size": 11.9552001953125}}, {"id_box": 27023, "box": [90.44117647058823, 253.02755271464662, 844.1259207516341, 261.2705198863635], "id_box_line": 9, "box_line": [90.44117647058823, 376.7938178661617, 844.121834150327, 13.73941319444441], "text": "automated procedure generates improvements in efficiency (relative to static MCMC algorithms)", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/JJXYBJ+CMR12", "size": 11.9552001953125}}, {"id_box": 27023, "box": [90.44117647058823, 253.02755271464662, 844.1259207516341, 261.2705198863635], "id_box_line": 10, "box_line": [90.44117647058823, 407.734077020202, 844.1259207516341, 13.739413194444523], "text": "ranging between one and three orders of magnitude. In each case, the automated procedure pro-", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/JJXYBJ+CMR12", "size": 11.9552001953125}}, {"id_box": 27023, "box": [90.44117647058823, 253.02755271464662, 844.1259207516341, 261.2705198863635], "id_box_line": 11, "box_line": [90.44117647058823, 438.67560448232325, 844.1179485294117, 13.73941319444441], "text": "duced an MCMC algorithm at least as efficient as any model-specific MCMC algorithm making use", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/JJXYBJ+CMR12", "size": 11.9552001953125}}, {"id_box": 27023, "box": [90.44117647058823, 253.02755271464662, 844.1259207516341, 261.2705198863635], "id_box_line": 12, "box_line": [90.44117647058823, 469.6171319444445, 844.121834150327, 13.73941319444441], "text": "of prior knowledge or expert opinion. In all examples, our iterative procedure terminated within", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/JJXYBJ+CMR12", "size": 11.9552001953125}}, {"id_box": 27023, "box": [90.44117647058823, 253.02755271464662, 844.1259207516341, 261.2705198863635], "id_box_line": 13, "box_line": [90.44117647058823, 500.55865940656565, 807.5319133986927, 13.739413194444467], "text": "four iterations, although it is plausible that for more complex models it would proceed longer.", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/JJXYBJ+CMR12", "size": 11.9552001953125}}, {"id_box": 27024, "box": [90.44117647058823, 531.5001868686869, 844.1279640522876, 385.03532907196967], "id_box_line": 14, "box_line": [119.84962900326798, 531.5001868686869, 814.7163460784315, 13.73941319444441], "text": "Our study has been confined to a single dimension of a much broader problem. We have strictly", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/JJXYBJ+CMR12", "size": 11.9552001953125}}, {"id_box": 27024, "box": [90.44117647058823, 531.5001868686869, 844.1279640522876, 385.03532907196967], "id_box_line": 15, "box_line": [90.44117647058823, 562.441714330808, 844.1260212418301, 13.73941319444441], "text": "considered combinations of scalar and blocked adaptive Metropolis-Hastings sampling, with a small", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/JJXYBJ+CMR12", "size": 11.9552001953125}}, {"id_box": 27024, "box": [90.44117647058823, 531.5001868686869, 844.1279640522876, 385.03532907196967], "id_box_line": 16, "box_line": [90.44117647058823, 593.3819734848485, 501.5604027777778, 13.739426136363647], "text": "number of exceptions only for the purpose of comparison (", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/JJXYBJ+CMR12", "size": 11.9552001953125}}, {"id_box": 27024, "box": [90.44117647058823, 531.5001868686869, 844.1279640522876, 385.03532907196967], "id_box_line": 17, "box_line": [591.9911115196079, 593.3819734848485, 30.034509803921537, 13.739426136363647], "text": "e.g.", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/QQLOWF+CMTI12", "size": 11.9552001953125}}, {"id_box": 27024, "box": [90.44117647058823, 531.5001868686869, 844.1279640522876, 385.03532907196967], "id_box_line": 18, "box_line": [622.0259730392157, 593.3819734848485, 312.5431674836601, 13.739426136363647], "text": ", the use of conjugate sampling). No", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/JJXYBJ+CMR12", "size": 11.9552001953125}}, {"id_box": 27024, "box": [90.44117647058823, 531.5001868686869, 844.1279640522876, 385.03532907196967], "id_box_line": 19, "box_line": [90.44122839052288, 624.3235009469697, 844.1258688316994, 13.739413194444467], "text": "less, we have restricted ourselves to non-overlapping sampling: each model parameter may only be", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/JJXYBJ+CMR12", "size": 11.9552001953125}}, {"id_box": 27024, "box": [90.44117647058823, 531.5001868686869, 844.1279640522876, 385.03532907196967], "id_box_line": 20, "box_line": [90.44122839052288, 655.265028409091, 844.1139104983661, 13.739413194444467], "text": "sampled by a single MCMC sampler function. We may instead view the domain of our problem (au-", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/JJXYBJ+CMR12", "size": 11.9552001953125}}, {"id_box": 27024, "box": [90.44117647058823, 531.5001868686869, 844.1279640522876, 385.03532907196967], "id_box_line": 21, "box_line": [90.44122839052288, 686.2065558712122, 844.1221004493465, 13.739439078282771], "text": "tomated determination of an efficient MCMC algorithm) as a broader space of MCMC algorithms.", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/JJXYBJ+CMR12", "size": 11.9552001953125}}, {"id_box": 27024, "box": [90.44117647058823, 531.5001868686869, 844.1279640522876, 385.03532907196967], "id_box_line": 22, "box_line": [90.44122839052288, 717.1481221590909, 844.1259693218955, 13.73941319444441], "text": "This space may permit a wide range of sampling algorithms not considered herein: auxiliary vari-", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/JJXYBJ+CMR12", "size": 11.9552001953125}}, {"id_box": 27024, "box": [90.44117647058823, 531.5001868686869, 844.1279640522876, 385.03532907196967], "id_box_line": 23, "box_line": [90.44122839052288, 748.0896755050505, 844.1259693218955, 13.73941319444441], "text": "able algorithms such as slice sampling (Neal, 2003), or derivative-based sampling algorithms such", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/JJXYBJ+CMR12", "size": 11.9552001953125}}, {"id_box": 27024, "box": [90.44117647058823, 531.5001868686869, 844.1279640522876, 385.03532907196967], "id_box_line": 24, "box_line": [90.44122839052288, 779.0299217171718, 844.11381000817, 13.739413194444438], "text": "as Hamiltonian Monte Carlo (Duane et al., 1987), among many possibilities. The resulting com-", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/JJXYBJ+CMR12", "size": 11.9552001953125}}, {"id_box": 27024, "box": [90.44117647058823, 531.5001868686869, 844.1279640522876, 385.03532907196967], "id_box_line": 25, "box_line": [90.44122839052288, 809.9714621212122, 844.1140109885621, 13.739413194444438], "text": "binatorial explosion in the space of MCMC algorithms makes any process of trial-and-error, or an", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/JJXYBJ+CMR12", "size": 11.9552001953125}}, {"id_box": 27024, "box": [90.44117647058823, 531.5001868686869, 844.1279640522876, 385.03532907196967], "id_box_line": 26, "box_line": [90.44122839052288, 840.9130025252525, 844.1258688316994, 13.739426136363647], "text": "attempt at comprehensive exploration, futile. It is for this reason we seek to develop an automated", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/JJXYBJ+CMR12", "size": 11.9552001953125}}, {"id_box": 27024, "box": [90.44117647058823, 531.5001868686869, 844.1279640522876, 385.03532907196967], "id_box_line": 27, "box_line": [90.44122839052288, 871.8545558712121, 844.1097234068628, 13.739413194444438], "text": "procedure for determining an efficient MCMC algorithm, which may not be globally, maximally", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/JJXYBJ+CMR12", "size": 11.9552001953125}}, {"id_box": 27024, "box": [90.44117647058823, 531.5001868686869, 844.1279640522876, 385.03532907196967], "id_box_line": 28, "box_line": [90.44122839052288, 902.7961014520203, 626.7281253676472, 13.739414488636356], "text": "efficient, but provides non-trivial improvements in efficiency, nonetheless.", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/JJXYBJ+CMR12", "size": 11.9552001953125}}, {"id_box": 27025, "box": [119.84968092320261, 933.7376379734849, 814.7160931781045, 13.739424842171715], "id_box_line": 29, "box_line": [119.84968092320261, 933.7376379734849, 814.7160931781045, 13.739424842171715], "text": "It should be noted that aspects of the problem addressed herein superficially resemble, but", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/JJXYBJ+CMR12", "size": 11.9552001953125}}, {"id_box": 27026, "box": [502.69723161764705, 983.0567062184343, 19.606558415032737, 13.739424842171719], "id_box_line": 30, "box_line": [502.69723161764705, 983.0567062184343, 19.606558415032737, 13.739424842171719], "text": "28", "category": "Page-footer", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/JJXYBJ+CMR12", "size": 11.9552001953125}}]}